 Kingdom","Broseley, Shropshire, England":"Broseley, Shropshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Dover, Kent, England":"Dover, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Astley, Shropshire, England":"Astley, Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Perverell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Peverall  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peverall","meanings":["Norman, English: relationship name from Old French  <i>Peurel</i> (Latin  <i>Piperellus</i>), a diminutive of Old French  <i>pevre</i> ‘pepper’ (Anglo-Norman French  <i>peivere</i>, Latin  <i>piper</i>), originally perhaps used as a nickname on the Continent but used as a personal name in Anglo-Norman England."]}]},{"name":"Melete","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of   Margareta ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mereta","meanings":["vernacular form of   Margareta ."]},{"name":"Mette","meanings":["vernacular form of   Margareta ."]},{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Melete Perverell married Warin de Burwardeslegh about 1173, in Astley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 4 daughters."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1142–1205":"1142–1205","1174–1202":"1174–1202","1174–1205":"1174–1205","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1183–1259":"1183–1259","1187–1218":"1187–1218","–Female":"Surnud","about 1183":"umbes 1183","about 1173":"umbes 1173","1187":"1187","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1240":"1240","1183":"1183","1180":"1180","Abt 1174":"umbes 1174","1205":"1205","1259":"1259","ABT 1187":"umbes 1187","1202":"1202","1178":"1178","1218":"1218",",Esseleghe,Stafford,England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Broseley, Shropshire, England":"Broseley, Shropshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Dover, Kent, England":"Dover, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Astley, Shropshire, England":"Astley, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1142–1205":"1142–1205","1174–1202":"1174–1202","1174–1205":"1174–1205","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1183–1259":"1183–1259","1187–1218":"1187–1218","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1183":"noin 1183","about 1173":"noin 1173","1187":"1187","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1240":"1240","1183":"1183","1180":"1180","Abt 1174":"noin 1174","1205":"1205","1259":"1259","ABT 1187":"noin 1187","1202":"1202","1178":"1178","1218":"1218",",Esseleghe,Stafford,England":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Broseley, Shropshire, England":"Broseley, Shropshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Dover, Kent, England":"Dover, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Astley, Shropshire, England":"Astley, Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée",